9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 351, L.D. 532, “An Act to Protect Health
10 Care Workers by Addressing Assaults in Health Care Settings”
11 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
12 'Sec. 2. 22 MRSA §1718-K is enacted to read:
13 §1718-K. Posting of information regarding crime of assault on health care worker
14 A health care entity shall post signage in a conspicuous location within each health care
15 facility of the health care entity that contains information regarding the criminal penalties
16 for assault on a health care worker pursuant to Title 17-A, section 752-F. The information
17 must include the unlawful conduct and the associated penalties if a person is found guilty
18 of the crime of assault on a health care worker. As used in this section, "health care entity"
19 has the same meaning as in section 1718-B, subsection 1, paragraph B and "health care
20 facility" has the same meaning as in section 1711-C, subsection 1, paragraph D.'
21 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
22 number to read consecutively.
23 SUMMARY
2244 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, requires that a health
2255 care entity post signage in health care facilities that contains information regarding the
2266 crime of assault on a health care worker. The signage must include information on the
2277 unlawful conduct and the associated penalties if a person is found guilty of assaulting a
2288 health care worker.
2299 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3300 (See attached)
